      "date": "2014-03-06 01:32:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 5.9/x86_64, CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/5d1331e2-a4c9-11e3-a92a-52540035b04c).  Ran 16 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7e6b3236e45ffdf5a29c87260763d08cc3bd6a25",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-03-24 08:43:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI do not think we need this debug patch, because according to LU-3949 description, when umount hung, it may takes hours, so if the issue is easy to be reproduced, then we have enough time to collect any logs or stack trace at that time, such as \"echo t > /proc/sysrq-trigger\".  Otherwise if it is difficult to be produced, for most of cases the client does not hung at umount, then your patch will cause a lot of noisy but unnecessary debug logs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ac0521cea9d2d19210a4f5b64da86260d10c84da",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 144,
        "name": "Hongchao Zhang",
        "email": "hongchao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "Hongchao.zhang"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-18 09:30:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nthe logs and stack traces don't contain useful information, which was mentions in LU-3949, then we should use some means\nto catch some logs to track the issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b93d9b58c191504b46ae390e37c54b740e0ec7d8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-04-22 07:52:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBut your patch just call dump_stack(), which output is NOT more than the way \"echo t > /proc/sysrq-trigger\". The later one can output more information, such as stack, memory.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
